Your container should be well drained and at least 2' deep and equally as wide. Keeping in mind how tall the plant grows, you may need to invest in a weighted pot (or pour in some concrete) so that it doesn't get too top heavy and topple over. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/Grow-Sunchokes-or-Jerusalem-Artichokes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Grow-Sunchokes-or-Jerusalem-Artichokes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/Grow-Sunchokes-or-Jerusalem-Artichokes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Grow-Sunchokes-or-Jerusalem-Artichokes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
